; 17 people are hospitalized, including 4 in intensive care; 50 patients are recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-covid-19-mayotte-191-cas-confirmes-au-total|title=Coronavirus COVID-19 \u00e0 Mayotte : 191 cas confirm\u00e9s au total|website=www.mayotte.ars.sante.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n<br>\nThe report of the Scientific Counsil on the Evolution of the Coronavirus in the Overseas Territories has been released which calls for strict confinement, doubling of hospital capactity. The situation in Mayotte is considered worrying and therefore calls for an \"extra-hospital\" structure to isolate the asymptomatic cases. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/coronavirus-le-conseil-scientifique-craint-une-aggravation-de-la-situation-outre-mer-et-preconise-le-maintien-strict-du-confinement-821800.html|title=Coronavirus: the scientific council fears a worsening of the Overseas situation and recommends \"the strict maintenance of confinement\"|language=fr|access-date=12 April 2020|website=Guyane la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 April, a third death was declared; the number of cases increases slightly to 196.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-mayotte-enregistre-un-3eme-deces-lie-au-covid-19-822004.html|title=Coronavirus : Mayotte enregistre un 3\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s li\u00e9 au COVID-19|website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 April, there are 203 confirmed cases of which 41 are health workers. 67 people have recovered, and more than 1,400 tests have been performed thus far. <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mayotte/coronavirus-le-cap-des-200-cas-est-franchi-a-mayotte-822244.html |title=Coronavirus : Le cap des 200 cas est franchi \u00e0 Mayotte |website=Mayotte la 1\u00e8re |language=fr-FR |access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{{Graph:Chart\n| type = area\n| linewidth = 1\n| showSymbols = 1\n| yTyp