2012\u2013present\n| television         = ''[[I Am Not Okay with This]]''\n}}\n'''Wyatt Jess Oleff'''<ref name=\"PulseSpikes\">{{cite news |title='IT' star Wyatt Oleff says the movie is \"a coming of age story\" |url=http://pulsespikes.com/it-star-wyatt-oleff-says-the-movie-is-a-coming-of-age-story/ |date=20 September 2017 |access-date=12 September 2019 |work=PulseSpikes |first=Ana |last=Sandoval |editor-first=Natalie |editor-last=Guardado |publisher=[[World Press]] Group, Inc.}}</ref> (born July 13, 2003) is an American actor, known for portraying the role of Stanley Uris in the 2017 [[supernatural horror film]] ''[[It (2017 film)|It]]'' and its [[It \u2013 Chapter Two|2019 sequel]], as well as the role of Stanley Barber in the [[coming-of-age]] [[comedy-drama]] [[web television]] series ''[[I Am Not Okay With This]]''.<ref name=\"NYDailyNews\">{{cite news |title='It' star Wyatt Oleff on the Losers Club's battle with Pennywise, what sets the remake apart |newspaper=[[New York Daily News]] |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/star-wyatt-oleff-losers-club-battle-pennywise-article-1.3480497 |first=Caitlyn |last=Hitt |date=8 September 2017 |access-date=12 September 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190530175756/https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/star-wyatt-oleff-losers-club-battle-pennywise-article-1.3480497 |archive-date=30 May 2019}}</ref> Oleff also had a minor role in the [[Marvel Studios]] films ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy (film)|Guardians of the Galaxy]]'' and ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'', as the young [[Star-Lord|Peter Quill]].\n\n== Early life ==\nOleff was born in [[Chicago, Illinois]], to Doug and Jennifer Oleff, living there for the first seven years of his life.<ref name=\"PulseSpikes\"/> He then moved to [[Los Angeles]] with his parents and began acting.<ref name=\"PulseSpikes\"/> One of his earliest acting roles was in a commercial for [[Coldwell Banker]].<ref name=\"PulseSpikes\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\